{
  "version": 1,
  "tasks": [
    {
      "id": "RQ-0957",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Migrate Ralph defaults from .json to .jsonc with automatic upgrade",
      "description": "Switch Ralph runtime/config defaults to .jsonc while preserving read support for legacy .json files. New projects initialized by Ralph must create .jsonc files by default. When both .json and .jsonc variants exist in a repo, Ralph must prefer the .jsonc variant. On the next Ralph run for legacy repos, migrate .ralph/*.json files to .jsonc safely and update references so future operations use .jsonc. Include project-level .gitignore handling so Ralph-managed ignore patterns move from .json to .jsonc entries during initialization and migration flows. Cover edge cases to prevent data loss or split-brain behavior during mixed-extension transitions.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "feature",
        "migration",
        "jsonc",
        "queue",
        "config",
        "init",
        "gitignore"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/constants.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/config/resolution.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/init/writers.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/init/gitignore.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/migration/file_migrations.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/migration/registry.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/migration/mod.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/doctor/project.rs",
        "crates/ralph/tests/",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/QueueFileWatcher.swift",
        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/RalphModels.swift",
        "README.md",
        "docs/configuration.md",
        "docs/features/migrations.md",
        "schemas/config.schema.json",
        "schemas/queue.schema.json",
        "make agent-ci",
        "ralph queue validate"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "user request: switch defaults to .jsonc, retain .json support, prefer .jsonc when both exist, migrate on next run, and update Ralph-related .gitignore entries.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/constants.rs :: DEFAULT_QUEUE_FILE/DEFAULT_DONE_FILE/DEFAULT_CONFIG_FILE currently point to .json paths.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/config/resolution.rs :: prefer_json_then_jsonc() and resolver comments indicate current precedence checks .json before .jsonc.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/init/writers.rs :: init writes/targets .ralph/queue.json, .ralph/done.json, and .ralph/config.json.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/migration/file_migrations.rs :: queue/done json->jsonc migration helpers exist; config path references remain .ralph/config.json.",
        "path: docs/configuration.md :: docs currently describe .json precedence and .json default paths.",
        "path: apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/QueueFileWatcher.swift :: watcher list currently monitors queue.json/done.json/config.json filenames."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Inventory all Ralph file-path defaults and extension precedence logic, then centralize extension selection so .jsonc is the canonical default everywhere.",
        "Update init/default writers and path resolution to emit/read .jsonc by default while still accepting legacy .json when .jsonc is absent.",
        "Implement and register next-run migration for legacy .ralph/queue.json, .ralph/done.json, and .ralph/config.json to .jsonc with safe rename semantics and reference rewrites.",
        "Implement .gitignore transition logic for Ralph-managed patterns so new repos ignore .jsonc files and migrating repos replace Ralph .json ignore entries with .jsonc entries.",
        "Update downstream consumers (parallel sync, doctor checks, macOS watcher/model messaging, docs, schemas, and CLI help text) to reflect .jsonc defaults and .json compatibility behavior.",
        "Add/adjust regression tests covering: init defaults, preference when both extensions exist, migration applicability/execution, .gitignore rewrites, and mixed-state edge cases.",
        "Run verification (`make agent-ci` plus targeted migration/config tests) and confirm migration smoke scenarios succeed without queue/done/config drift."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "Let's switch from using .json files to using .jsonc. Any ralph files that currently use the .jsn extension should now default to using .jsonc. Maintain support for .json but make all new projects use .jsonc by default via init and if a repo has both .json and .jsonc files prefer the .jsonc version. If a project is currently using .json file extensions, on the next run of ralph migrate the files to use .jsonc instead. Make sure we also consider modifying the project .gitignore, not this specific project in particular, any project that is using ralph. If they have any ralph .json files in its .gitignore file we should change that to be .jsonc ignored instead since the migration to .jsonc must take place. consider all edge cases to ensure a smooth transition for all projects using ralph.",
      "created_at": "2026-02-22T00:12:09Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-02-22T00:12:09Z",
      "depends_on": [],
      "blocks": [],
      "relates_to": [],
      "custom_fields": {
        "migration_mode": "json_to_jsonc",
        "project_type": "code"
      }
    },
